morphology

definition.value: A quality of a single physical entity inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer's size or shape or structure.

label.value: shape
structure

definition.value: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's relative position, shape, arrangements and connectivity of an organism's various parts; the pattern underlying its form.

label.value: behavioral quality

definition.value: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's behavior aggregate of the responses or reactions or movements in a given situation.

label.value: branched

definition.value: A quality which inheres in a continuant.

label.value: organismal quality

definition.value: A quality that inheres in an entire organism or part of an organism.

handedness

definition.value: A behavioral quality inhering ina bearer by virtue of the bearer's unequal distribution of fine motor skill between its left and right hands or feet.

label.value: left handedness

definition.value: Handedness where the organism preferentially uses the left hand or foot for tasks requiring the use of a single hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.

label.value: right handedness

definition.value: Handedness where the organism preferentially uses the right hand or foot for tasks requiring the use of a single hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.

label.value: ambidextrous handedness

definition.value: Handedness where the organism exhibits no overall dominance in the use of right or left hand or foot in the performance of tasks that require one hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.
